.cs 3 on
.item 'SHOW PORT Command' 'Updated on 11/15/84 by AEH'
.itemix "'SHOW PORTS Command'"
.boxon
SHOW {PORT|PORTS [[front-end|CONSOLE|ASYNC|PDP|SNA|VIRTUAL]
.*               <---------------------------------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SHOW PORT front-end CONSOLE ASYNC PDP SNA VIRTUAL
                 [DIRECT|LEASED|DIAL]|ALL] [collect-options]}
.*               <------------------> <--> <--------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SHOW PORT DIRECT LEASED DIAL
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SHOW PORT ALL
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SHOW PORT collect-options
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SHOW PORT or SHOW PORTS command displays the status of a particular port,
all ports, or all the ports connected to a particular front end.

.* SELECT 'SHOW PORT Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION FRONT-END
.ix front-end 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
front-end\\\\\\\the name of a particular communications controller (e.g.,
                1270A).

.* OPTION CONSOLE
.ix 'CONSOLE Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
CONSOLE\\\\\\\\\ports connected to the operator consoles.

.* OPTION ASYNC
.ix 'ASYNC Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
ASYNC\\\\\\\\\\\asynchronous ports.

.* OPTION PDP
.ix 'PDP Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
PDP\\\\\\\\\\\\\ports connected via the PDP front ends.

.* OPTION SNA
.ix 'SNA Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
SNA\\\\\\\\\\\\\ports connected via the SNA (VTAM) network.

.* OPTION VIRTUAL
.ix 'VIRTUAL Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
VIRTUAL\\\\\\\\\ports being used as "virtual terminals" (i.e., batch).

.* OPTION DIRECT
.ix 'DIRECT Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
DIRECT\\\\\\\\\\ports connected directly (terminals with dedicated ports).

.* OPTION LEASED
.ix 'LEASED Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
LEASED\\\\\\\\\\leased direct ports (i.e., bulk rate).

.* OPTION DIAL
.ix 'DIAL Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
DIAL\\\\\\\\\\\\ports connected via the dial-up ports.

.* OPTION ALL
.ix 'ALL Option' 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
ALL\\\\\\\\\\\\\all ports connected to all the front ends.

.* OPTION COLLECT-OPTIONS,BY,KEEP,NOCLEAR,NOCLR,CLEAR,CLR,WARN,NOWARN
.optix collect-options
.ix collect-options 'on SHOW PORTS Command'
collect-options\allow you to insert the system response to the SHOW PORT or
                SHOW PORTS command into your active file.  Type HELP
                COLLECT-OPTIONS for a description of these options.
.cs 3 off
